                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Was asked to keep kinda quiet on it till we got a chance to test it on beta, but heres the skinny of the new system.
<br />

<br />
There is now the capability to give each individual mob a seperate damage table (no its not a fixed percent) that they will use when charmed, this can be the same as, higher, or lower then the mobs normal damage table.  
<br />

<br />
Currently in most OOW zones the DPS = 1/2 of what an equivelant god mob would charm for.  This is still being tuned, and each and EVERY enchanter needs to feedback this as they begin charming in the new OOW zones.  It would be a bit different, but they didn't activate the new charm spells/system until a few days before the end of beta.
<br />

<br />
Old charm spells are not on this new system, although they could later be retroed (not planned at this time)
<br />

<br />
OOW charms work in pop and god (only partially implemented in god) and they can (not 100 percent sure, but im pushing for it) go back and flag every trash mob from Kodtaz to Txevu charmable.
<br />

<br />
Ancient Voice of Muram: is a level 70 cap (currently highest charm possible) spell and lasts something like 8 ticks fixed, and its 1000 resist check
<br />

<br />
True Name: stat wise is the same model and CoD but uses the new system and a 69 cap on charm (1 higher then bard voice of vampire), this will be our bread and butter, but is also outside the foci range for saving mana 
<br />

<br />
Compel: another CoD clone but 67 cap, and does fall within the GoD foci range
<br />

<br />
<span style="color: blue">Why am I supporting this system?</span>  First off, it makes 95 percent of level equivelant mobs charmable (a good portion of xp mobs fall in this range, until you get past wall of slaughter to the raid/xp zones. Secondly, we've now opened the door for charm type foci, to include faster casting time, increased duration, and increased resist check types for future expansions.  This will allow charm to remain viable into th e future instead of recieving expansions like GoD where you are given 1 mob type in only a few trash zones and then told too bad so sad no charm for the rest of the expansion.  Third, this system is still brand new and the damage tables are open to feedback, parse your lil chanty hearts out but make sure to get a few key things like your charisma score, what debuffs your using, the mob level and name, average duration of charm, what buffs on pet, and pets DPS.  Post them in the Facts section.
<br />

<br />
For the record, this new charm table system is for every OOW charm for every class.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://dictionary.reference.com/search?r=67&q=Sell%20Out" target="_blank" class="postlink"><img src="http://www.therunes.net/forums/files/nanyea.gif" border="0" /></a>
<br />
<a href="http://www.TheRunes2.c__" target="_blank">www.TheRunes2.c__</a> sell out.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
